Path: godot/classes/class_label.rst
Summary: This section describes the theme properties available for customizing the appearance of a Label node, including colors, spacing, outline, shadow, font, and style boxes.

Theme Property Descriptions
*   font_color (Color): Default text Color of the Label. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
*   font_outline_color (Color): The color of text outline. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1).
*   font_shadow_color (Color): Color of the text's shadow effect. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 0).
*   line_spacing (int): Additional vertical spacing between lines (in pixels), spacing is added to line descent. This value can be negative. Default: 3.
*   outline_size (int): Text outline size. Note: If using a font with FontFile.multichannel_signed_distance_field enabled, its FontFile.msdf_pixel_range must be set to at least *twice* the value of outline_size for outline rendering to look correct. Otherwise, the outline may appear to be cut off earlier than intended. Note: Using a value that is larger than half the font size is not recommended, as the font outline may fail to be fully closed in this case. Default: 0.
*   paragraph_spacing (int): Vertical space between paragraphs. Added on top of line_spacing. Default: 0.
*   shadow_offset_x (int): The horizontal offset of the text's shadow. Default: 1.
*   shadow_offset_y (int): The vertical offset of the text's shadow. Default: 1.
*   shadow_outline_size (int): The size of the shadow outline. Default: 1.
*   font (Font): Font used for the Label's text.
*   font_size (int): Font size of the Label's text.
*   focus (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the Label is focused (when used with assistive apps).
*   normal (StyleBox): Background StyleBox for the Label.